args:
Malinda is revealed to be Chronos, who plots to
use the prince to eliminate Vania. When the
prince and Chronos clash over Vania's fate,
the war god Grimnir appears, offering his help
in defeating the time-wielding menace.
Don't worry, you guys!\nYou know I'm super strong, right?
But there're so many of them!
It won't matter HOW many there are\nonce I get serious!
Hngh! Ugh...RUDE! If you're trying\nto make me mad, it's working!
I'm... I'm fine! Peachy, even.\nI'm a super strong vampire!
You saved us that other time too,\nbut we all got scared, and...
And that must not have felt very nice.\nSo we all wanted to say we're sorry.
You don't have to apologize. I, uh...\nI TOTALLY knew you didn't mean it,\nso it didn't even bother me at all. Yup.
You're the best, Vania.\nAnd thank you!
Jeez, you're slow. Show's over already!
Apologies, my liege. It seems I was an\nunsatisfactory guide, so our arrival was\ndelayed.
You were a fine guide. I just...
(I couldn't stop thinking about that voice's\nwarning, wondering if Malinda...if Chronos\nwasn't leading me into a trap.)
Ooh, there they are! It looks like Vania\nand the kids still have all their bits intact!
That's a relief. {player_name}\nseems fine as well.
We heard fighting, so we came running,\nbut...looks like we're late to the party.
SUPER late! Not a single one of you made\nit here on time!
I'm especially disappointed in you,\nbloodkin. You need to get used to being\nat my beck and call, stat! Is that clear?
GOOD! If anything happened to me,\nyou'd be... Huh? I'm kinda...
Something feels...funny.\nLike my whole body's going...numb...
You know what's happening to her?
She has overexerted herself. Her reserves\nof vampiric power might have run dry.
Since coming to the Halidom, she has not\nimbibed a single drop of human blood.
Blood is the root of all vampires' strength.\nWithout it, they inevitably wither.
And yet she has now twice used her power\nto eliminate these fiends. At this rate, her\nlife is in danger.
(This is my fault. If I'd trusted Malinda,\nI could have made it here sooner.)
(If I'd been here to fight, she wouldn't\nhave expended so much of her power...)
But...that means she'll be okay if she gets\nsome of the ol' red-and-sloshy, right?
...{player_name}. I humbly ask\nthat you share your blood with my liege.
She requires the most potent blood\npossible to ensure her survival.
In that regard, yours is quite sufficient.\nIt would serve as an unparalleled panacea\nfor her affliction.
But if a vampire drinks your blood, don't\nyou become a bloodkin or whatever and\nhave to do everything they say?
You need not fear that. Only by sinking\nher fangs into the subject and drinking\nfrom them directly is a bloodkin created.
If you spill your own blood and grant it to\nher, it will not constitute a bloodkin's pact.
Please, sir. I beg you, save her life.
Vania, can you hear me? Drink this.\nIt will help restore your strength.
She looks like she's in pain!\nWhat's wrong?!
Malinda! Are you sure she'll be all right?!
For strong medicine is also potent poison.\nA vampire so young as Vania will not be\nable to withstand your blood.
I do thank you for your blithe cooperation,\n{player_name}. With your aid, I\ncan fulfill my purpose here.
Indeed. All is as you suspect, vessel.
You ARE Chronos! Dammit!\nWhat are you plotting this time?!
I see little point in explaining. I shall\nexecute my duties and nothing more.
My bonds will see that you behave yourself\nuntil my task is done.
Now, make your peace, princess of the\nnight. For my true liege cannot permit the\nseeds of future threat to germinate.
So it's Vania you're after?! Rngh... Must...\nsave her!
That's far enough, man-wrought wyrm\nwho would toy with time.
Heh. If an introduction is what you seek,\nI shall gladly oblige.
For I am a god of war and Tuner of\nfate's melody. The gale that sweeps the\nfield of battle. The mad cyclone, Grimnir!
We meet at last, Prince. But I fear we've\nnot the time to celebrate until this dragon\nwho would spurn fate's designs is undone!
Now, stand! Arise, O Prince and his allies!\nLet us slay the wicked wyrm together, and\ngrant succor to the uncanny princess!
Thank you, Grimnir.\nChronos, your scheming ends here!
Foolish vessel. None will be permitted to\nstand in the way of my true liege's grand\ndesign.
I shall see you and this Tuner alike\nbanished beyond the reaches of time!
